c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/marathon-bungie-runner-extraction-hardcore-1851775956\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/marathon-bungie-runner-extraction-hardcore-1851775956\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eMarathon\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e is out in less than six months and there’s still a lot we don’t know about it. But thanks to the current closed alpha, we’ve had a chance to finally go hands-on with Bungie’s first new project in over a decade and the latest live-service game coming out of the PlayStation portfolio. The results so far have left us scratching out heads. - Zack Zwiezen \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/marathon-alpha-review-impressions-bungie-extraction-fps-1851777775\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/marathon-alpha-review-impressions-bungie-extraction-fps-1851777775\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"d529e2ad9861c4320e7ba08169c631d7\" data-recommend-id=\"image://d529e2ad9861c4320e7ba08169c631d7\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1648\" data-height=\"927\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A gallery in 2062, with Fia and another character discussing one of the paintings.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"A gallery in 2062, with Fia and another character discussing one of the paintings.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/d529e2ad9861c4320e7ba08169c631d7.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/d529e2ad9861c4320e7ba08169c631d7.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/d529e2ad9861c4320e7ba08169c631d7.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A gallery in 2062, with Fia and another character discussing one of the paintings.\" data-chomp-id=\"d529e2ad9861c4320e7ba08169c631d7\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"927\" data-alt=\"A gallery in 2062, with Fia and another character discussing one of the paintings.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/d529e2ad9861c4320e7ba08169c631d7.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: Wadjet Eye Games / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"d529e2ad9861c4320e7ba08169c631d7\" data-recommend-id=\"image://d529e2ad9861c4320e7ba08169c631d7\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1648\" data-height=\"927\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A gallery in 2062, with Fia and another character discussing one of the paintings.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eSeven years ago, Wadjet Eye Games released \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/best-point-and-click-adventure-games-unavowed-norco-1851774003/slides/2\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/best-point-and-click-adventure-games-unavowed-norco-1851774003/slides/2\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eUnavowed\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, a point-and-click adventure that took the industry by surprise. Incorporating ideas from BioWare RPGs, this was a game in which the companions you took with you for any mission changed not only how the puzzles were solved, but how the story was told. It was magnificent, and received wide acclaim. Wadjet Eye’s follow-up game, some seven years later, is \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://store.steampowered.com/app/1346360/Old_Skies/\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://store.steampowered.com/app/1346360/Old_Skies/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eOld Skies\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, and while its structure takes a more traditional shape, it’s a boldly ambitious, constantly inventive piece of masterful storytelling. - John Walker \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/old-skies-wadjet-eye-adventure-pc-steam-unavowed-1851777432\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/old-skies-wadjet-eye-adventure-pc-steam-unavowed-1851777432\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"9db371b5d6127298df92e1e04ae31ace\" data-recommend-id=\"image://9db371b5d6127298df92e1e04ae31ace\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1274\" data-height=\"717\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Raz from Psychonauts wearing his googles, in a wooden room.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"Raz from Psychonauts wearing his googles, in a wooden room.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/9db371b5d6127298df92e1e04ae31ace.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/9db371b5d6127298df92e1e04ae31ace.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/9db371b5d6127298df92e1e04ae31ace.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Raz from Psychonauts wearing his googles, in a wooden room.\" data-chomp-id=\"9db371b5d6127298df92e1e04ae31ace\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"717\" data-alt=\"Raz from Psychonauts wearing his googles, in a wooden room.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/9db371b5d6127298df92e1e04ae31ace.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: Double Fine / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"9db371b5d6127298df92e1e04ae31ace\" data-recommend-id=\"image://9db371b5d6127298df92e1e04ae31ace\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1274\" data-height=\"717\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Raz from Psychonauts wearing his googles, in a wooden room.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eOne of the stranger moments of my career was reviewing a game, giving it a four-page review  and a well-deserved score of 89 percent in the then-massively-selling UK \u003cem\u003ePC Gamer\u003c/em\u003e magazine, and then the game not coming out for another eight months. That was just one example of the nightmares \u003cem\u003ePsychonauts—\u003c/em\u003eDouble Fine’s magnum opus—went through on its path to becoming one of the most beloved games of all time. It’s now 20 years since its official U.S. release, and that deserves celebration. - John Walker \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;I